metadata.name: Gradients of the Moon
metadata.description:
There is something magical about the period when the sun begins to set and the moon becomes visible in the sky.

The moon is one of my favorite subjects to shoot; itâ€™s so familiar yet so unfamiliar at the same time. Something that we see almost daily, but holds so much mystery and beauty as it cements itself in the sky.

This composition is a combination of four 35mm photos taken of the moon during different periods of sunset.
